00:00:09.670 --> 00:00:14.439
the denominators be the same. So, the first thing that we need to do is find a

00:00:14.451 --> 00:00:20.010
common denominator between 12 and 8. Using the factor tree method, I know that 4

00:00:20.022 --> 00:00:26.405
is a common factor for both 12 and 8. I know that 4 times 3 is 12. And 4 times 2

00:00:26.417 --> 00:00:32.359
gives me 8. So, I can multiply those together, which gives me a common

00:00:32.371 --> 00:00:38.271
denominator of 24. The next thing I need to do is create equivalent fractions

00:00:38.283 --> 00:00:43.919
that have 24 as the denominator. So, I need to create equivalent fraction for 7

00:00:43.931 --> 00:00:49.560
over 12. Since we want to have 24 in the denominator, I know I have to multiply

00:00:49.572 --> 00:00:54.930
12 by 2 to get 24 and whatever I multiply the denominator by, I also have to

00:00:54.942 --> 00:01:00.389
multiply the numerator by. So, an equivalent fraction for 7/12 is 14 over 24.

00:01:00.762 --> 00:01:07.524
Now, let's convert 3/8. We want 24 as the denominator. 8 times 3 gives us 24. 8

00:01:07.650 --> 00:01:14.576
